snippet: Rescuers pulled more bodies from the debris on Sunday after heavy rain in central Indonesia loosened soil and collapsed a hill.
abstract: Rescuers continue to pull bodies from debris after heavy rain in central Indonesia caused hill collapse; subsequent landslide killed at least 32 villagers and left 76 others missing.
lead_paragraph: Rescuers pulled more bodies from the debris on Sunday after heavy rain in central Indonesia loosened soil and collapsed a hill.
